---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`ARR (Annual Recurring Revenue) | ${siteName}`}
  description="ARR definition, how to calculate it from MRR, and when it’s a useful metric."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>ARR (Annual Recurring Revenue)</h1>
    <p>ARR is the annualized run-rate of recurring revenue. Most teams compute it as MRR × 12.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>When ARR is useful</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Comparing annualized run-rate across quarters.</li>
        <li>Communicating scale to investors and stakeholders (when revenue is mostly recurring).</li>
        <li>Normalizing monthly vs annual plans into a single run-rate number.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">When ARR misleads</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>If revenue is dominated by usage overages that swing month-to-month.</li>
        <li>If you have large one-time fees mixed into totals.</li>
        <li>If churn is high and you treat a short-lived customer as a 12-month run-rate.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/arr-calculator/">ARR calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/mrr-calculator/">MRR calculator</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/mrr/">MRR</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/churn/">Churn</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

